overview: The user's intent was to enhance a Sleep Questionnaire Application by
  adding persistent storage for questionnaire responses and providing a
  client-facing dashboard to access this data. The approach involved integrating
  a PostgreSQL database (NeonDB) using Prisma, developing API endpoints for
  saving and retrieving responses, and building a basic admin dashboard. A key
  decision was to simplify the authentication system from a custom HMAC-signed
  session to a more straightforward cookie-based approach leveraging Next.js
  middleware for route protection. This resulted in a functional system where
  questionnaire data is saved, and an authenticated client can view and export
  responses via a web dashboard. Testing confirmed the database integration, API
  functionality, and dashboard access, with a minor clarification needed
  regarding the form's "pre-fill" functionality versus actual submission.
